00:34:06,510 --> 00:34:08,478
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Charlotte, what are you doing?

520
00:34:08,912 --> 00:34:09,970
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thinking.

521
00:34:10,247 --> 00:34:12,238
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I do my best thinking upside down.

522
00:34:12,349 --> 00:34:14,579
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Blood goes to my head and perks me up.

523
00:34:14,985 --> 00:34:18,546
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}L've been thinking, too, you know, about Christmas.

524
00:34:19,456 --> 00:34:22,152
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't worry, Wilbur. We'll figure something out.

525
00:34:27,464 --> 00:34:29,762
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on, lke. Come on.

526
00:34:39,843 --> 00:34:41,276
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not to be too much trouble,

527
00:34:41,378 --> 00:34:43,938
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}but have you figured something out?

528
00:34:44,481 --> 00:34:47,143
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not yet, but it's like a web.

529
00:34:47,251 --> 00:34:51,779
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You make it, you wait, and something always comes.

530
00:34:52,155 --> 00:34:53,622
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good night, Charlotte.

531
00:34:54,057 --> 00:34:55,422
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good night, Wilbur.

532
00:34:59,429 --> 00:35:01,124
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And swing.

533
00:35:06,403 --> 00:35:08,030
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And stick.

534
00:35:08,405 --> 00:35:10,202
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And loop.

535
00:35:23,420 --> 00:35:26,878
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And back up, stick, and...

536
00:36:45,402 --> 00:36:47,597
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr. Zuckerman!

537
00:36:49,373 --> 00:36:52,570
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Okay, you gotta come see this.

538
00:37:00,617 --> 00:37:02,084
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on, Homer!

539
00:37:02,786 --> 00:37:03,878
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on!

540
00:37:48,665 --> 00:37:51,862
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- What's a "so me pig"? - It's "some pig."

541
00:37:52,969 --> 00:37:54,334
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's a miracle.

542
00:37:54,871 --> 00:37:57,305
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's nothing short of a bona fide miracle.

543
00:38:04,881 --> 00:38:06,280
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Minister Beecher?

544
00:38:07,584 --> 00:38:09,518
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Homer. Edith.

545
00:38:09,920 --> 00:38:11,649
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What brings you here?

546
00:38:12,255 --> 00:38:13,279
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Divinity?

547
00:38:15,659 --> 00:38:17,024
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We think so.

548
00:38:32,309 --> 00:38:36,405
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We'd better keep this quiet until l address it in my sermon.

549
00:38:36,780 --> 00:38:38,509
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You can't tell a soul, but you gotta come up to the barn.

550
00:38:38,615 --> 00:38:39,582
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Keep it between me and you.

551
00:38:39,750 --> 00:38:42,116
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Swing by the farm. - Okay. Goodbye.

552
00:38:49,926 --> 00:38:52,622
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now, don't tell nobody. Shouldn't get around.

553
00:38:54,865 --> 00:38:57,698
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's a word in a spider web at Zuckerman's barn.

554
00:39:18,255 --> 00:39:22,191
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Charlotte, what does a "some pig" do?

555
00:39:22,292 --> 00:39:25,090
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This isn't for what you do. It's for what you are.

556
00:39:25,462 --> 00:39:27,259
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Some pigs might smile a bit.

557
00:39:35,138 --> 00:39:37,606
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The lifting of the head, nice touch!

558
00:39:58,361 --> 00:40:02,195
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}As ugly as that spider is, we should have known she was smart.

559
00:40:02,299 --> 00:40:05,268
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So, you don't believe that someone might be smart and pretty?

560
00:40:05,368 --> 00:40:08,565
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No. Yes! L mean, yes, because you are.

561
00:40:08,672 --> 00:40:10,640
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Clever little spider, isn't she?

562
00:40:10,740 --> 00:40:12,799
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where's the spider who did this?

563
00:40:13,243 --> 00:40:17,202
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, we looked all over and couldn't find one.

564
00:40:23,019 --> 00:40:24,247
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Looks pretty good.

565
00:40:24,354 --> 00:40:26,948
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Still ain't gonna change anything. He's a goner.

566
00:40:27,057 --> 00:40:29,582
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah. Glad nobody eats cows.

567
00:40:30,126 --> 00:40:34,153
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Got to admit, that's a fine-looking pig. - Yep, that's some pig, all right.

568
00:40:42,239 --> 00:40:46,005
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}After a few weeks, the phenomenon of the web wore off.

569
00:40:47,043 --> 00:40:48,567
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Nobody cared anymore,

570
00:40:49,980 --> 00:40:54,076
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and what was amazing yesterday was suddenly ordinary again today.

571
00:40:55,852 --> 00:40:58,821
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It looked like Wilbur might not see snow after all.

572
00:41:03,927 --> 00:41:06,020
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Excuse me, but why are we here?

573
00:41:06,129 --> 00:41:09,565
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I mean, yes, barn meeting and so on and so forth. L understand that.

574
00:41:09,666 --> 00:41:14,194
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But must this concern us? And at such an ungodly hour!

575
00:41:14,304 --> 00:41:16,067
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You know, Wilbur's not the only one

576
00:41:16,172 --> 00:41:19,801
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}who could end up being Christmas dinner with an apple in his mouth.

577
00:41:20,277 --> 00:41:22,472
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good point. Yes. Carry on, then.

578
00:41:22,579 --> 00:41:25,207
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Ike, this involves every one of us.

579
00:41:25,315 --> 00:41:29,547
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I just have trouble looking at you. That's all.

580
00:41:29,753 --> 00:41:31,721
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This isn't about me. It's about Wilbur.

581
00:41:31,821 --> 00:41:35,382
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And, for the record, my view of you is not exactly a treat, either.

582
00:41:36,826 --> 00:41:40,057
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}As we have all seen, humans have very short attention spans,

583
00:41:40,163 --> 00:41:42,597
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and there's just too much time between now and Christmas.

584
00:41:42,699 --> 00:41:45,463
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Certainly enough time for Zuckerman to find his affection for a pig

585
00:41:45,568 --> 00:41:47,160
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}losing out to his hunger for ham.

586
00:41:47,270 --> 00:41:49,238
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- That spider can talk! - Yeah.

587
00:41:49,706 --> 00:41:51,139
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What did she say, exactly?

588
00:41:51,241 --> 00:41:54,677
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She said the farmer might possibly still slaughter the pig.

589
00:41:55,345 --> 00:41:58,872
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sorry, old chap, but it is a common fate for your ilk.

590
00:41:59,015 --> 00:42:00,573
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I could just bust through the fence again.

591
00:42:00,684 --> 00:42:02,515
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No. Once was enough for that.

592
00:42:02,619 --> 00:42:04,678
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I just have to get the right word written.

593
00:42:04,788 --> 00:42:06,881
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Something that makes Wilbur so special

594
00:42:06,990 --> 00:42:09,424
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}that Zuckerman will never think about killing him again.

595
00:42:09,526 --> 00:42:12,620
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You need something snappy, like "pig supreme."

596
00:42:12,729 --> 00:42:14,128
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That sounds like a dessert.

597
00:42:14,230 --> 00:42:16,357
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So, what's the point, anyway? It won't work.

598
00:42:16,466 --> 00:42:20,562
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Could you please, just once, say something-omething positive?

599
00:42:20,670 --> 00:42:22,900
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Okay. I'm positive it won't work.

600
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:26,307
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How about "harmoniously proportioned"?

601
00:42:26,409 --> 00:42:30,106
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Harmoniously proportioned, yes! - Stop that! You're following again.

602
00:42:30,213 --> 00:42:33,705
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Please, all of you! What's the perfect word for Wilbur?

603
00:42:33,817 --> 00:42:35,375
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How about "delicious"?

604
00:42:35,719 --> 00:42:38,813
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Or "nutritious"? Or "extra crispy"?

605
00:42:39,289 --> 00:42:40,415
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How about...

606
00:42:41,224 --> 00:42:44,091
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Did you get him? - Yep. Bull's-eye.

607
00:42:44,194 --> 00:42:46,594
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How about "terrific, terrific, terrific"?

608
00:42:46,696 --> 00:42:49,995
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good. Much too long, though. L've only got so much web.

609
00:42:50,100 --> 00:42:52,330
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But one "terrific" might work.

610
00:42:52,435 --> 00:42:56,132
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It simply isn't true. The pig is not terrific.

611
00:42:56,239 --> 00:42:59,402
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look at him! He's absolutely average.

612
00:42:59,943 --> 00:43:03,640
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If you wish to be truthful, then that is the word you should write.

613
00:43:03,747 --> 00:43:04,975
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Average."

614
00:43:05,148 --> 00:43:08,879
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wilbur, this only works if the word l write is true.

615
00:43:08,985 --> 00:43:11,920
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And only you can tell us which word that is.

616
00:43:12,022 --> 00:43:13,319
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So look around.

617
00:43:14,591 --> 00:43:16,855
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We've all gathered around to help you.

618
00:43:17,127 --> 00:43:19,459
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now tell everyone how you feel.

619
00:43:27,337 --> 00:43:30,135
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look, there's a red one! And a blue one!

620
00:43:31,074 --> 00:43:33,201
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Avery! You'll never catch me!

621
00:43:33,510 --> 00:43:35,375
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm going to get you!

622
00:43:37,247 --> 00:43:39,477
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look at the fireworks, Mom!

623
00:43:40,350 --> 00:43:42,978
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Avery, come on if you ever want to catch me!

624
00:43:58,501 --> 00:44:00,435
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This web thing is really paying off.

625
00:44:00,537 --> 00:44:02,572
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr. Zuckerman!

626
00:44:05,175 --> 00:44:09,271
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There it is, side to side, right in the same place. "Terrific."

627
00:44:10,113 --> 00:44:11,478
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It was the most amazing thing!

628
00:44:11,581 --> 00:44:15,176
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Last time we had hundreds of people. This time it's going to be thousands!

629
00:44:15,285 --> 00:44:17,810
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It says "terrific" just as clear as day.

630
00:44:17,921 --> 00:44:19,582
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}T-E-double-R-l-F-l-C.

631
00:44:19,689 --> 00:44:22,123
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I mean, can you imagine a spider being able to spell that word?

632
00:44:22,225 --> 00:44:24,489
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't think l could spell that word till the 10th grade.

633
00:44:36,306 --> 00:44:38,399
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Fifty cents. - Do you like that one, sir?

634
00:44:38,508 --> 00:44:40,013
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's going to be $1.

635
00:44:41,411 --> 00:44:43,140
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Wow! - Gather 'round, folks!

636
00:44:44,280 --> 00:44:47,408
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Remember, you saw it right here at Zuckerman's.

637
00:44:48,585 --> 00:44:52,214
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And, before you leave, don't forget to take some of our berries home with you!

638
00:44:52,322 --> 00:44:54,586
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- So, you think this might work? - Nope.

639
00:44:54,691 --> 00:44:57,125
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Dare l say it? He looks "terrific."

640
00:44:57,227 --> 00:44:58,194
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look at them all!

641
00:44:58,294 --> 00:45:01,422
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah. Smile pretty. I wish geese had teeth.

642
00:45:05,702 --> 00:45:08,000
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Been down here since dawn...

643
00:45:08,238 --> 00:45:11,674
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What are you suggesting? That Fern has something to do with all this?

644
00:45:12,008 --> 00:45:14,943
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How else could those words have gotten into that web?

645
00:45:15,245 --> 00:45:18,681
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know everyone is saying it's some kind of miracle, but...

646
00:45:18,781 --> 00:45:21,477
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But what? You don't think it is?

647
00:45:22,418 --> 00:45:23,578
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do you?

648
00:45:24,154 --> 00:45:27,282
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The web itself is a miracle.

649
00:45:28,191 --> 00:45:29,624
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wouldn't you agree?

650
00:45:30,994 --> 00:45:32,621
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, can you spin one?

651
00:45:33,196 --> 00:45:36,654
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I can crochet a doily. - Because someone taught you how.

652
00:45:37,100 --> 00:45:40,467
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Nobody teaches a spider. They just know how to spin a web.

653
00:45:40,570 --> 00:45:42,367
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't you think that's a miracle?

654
00:45:47,277 --> 00:45:50,576
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}As summer ended, so did the excitement about the web.

655
00:45:51,181 --> 00:45:53,843
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Charlotte needed to think of something special.

656
00:45:54,584 --> 00:45:57,951
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Special enough to change the way people saw the world,

657
00:45:58,688 --> 00:46:01,088
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}or at least one pig in the world, anyway.

658
00:46:02,192 --> 00:46:06,561
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The truth is, Charlotte feared she would never find a word that could do all that.

659
00:46:07,363 --> 00:46:11,060
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And she had to hurry. Time was running out for her.

660
00:46:11,801 --> 00:46:15,737
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But once a promise is made, it needs to be kept.

661
00:46:17,106 --> 00:46:19,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Still no web, huh? - Nope.

662
00:46:19,776 --> 00:46:22,540
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I haven't seen one in, l'd say, at least a month.

663
00:46:23,813 --> 00:46:27,374
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Funny how you get used to all those people being around the place.

664
00:46:27,483 --> 00:46:29,713
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kind of quiet without them, isn't it?

665
00:46:32,222 --> 00:46:35,555
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I noticed the hinge pin's busted on the damper in the smokehouse.

666
00:46:35,658 --> 00:46:37,216
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Want me to order a new one?

667
00:46:37,527 --> 00:46:39,995
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Suppose you better. That's a special order.

668
00:46:40,530 --> 00:46:44,296
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Better get a jump on that if we're going to smoke any ham before the holidays.

669
00:46:44,400 --> 00:46:46,630
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We may need another cord of wood, too.

670
00:46:48,438 --> 00:46:51,930
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm just going to throw this out here one more time. "Pig supreme."

671
00:46:52,041 --> 00:46:54,635
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, Golly! Now you're just beating a dead horse.

672
00:46:54,744 --> 00:46:56,405
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Hey! - Sorry.

673
00:46:56,512 --> 00:46:59,813
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look, l don't come across many words in the field,

674
00:46:59,915 --> 00:47:01,949
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}other than "Hyah!" or "Giddyup!"

675
00:47:02,252 --> 00:47:05,187
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But that rat's always dragging in trash with writing on it.

676
00:47:05,288 --> 00:47:06,346
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}L agree.

677
00:47:06,456 --> 00:47:09,050
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's about time Templeton started pulling his weight around here

678
00:47:09,158 --> 00:47:10,648
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}instead of just eating it.

679
00:47:10,760 --> 00:47:12,523
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I bet he could bring us some choice words.

680
00:47:12,629 --> 00:47:16,622
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've got a choice word for you. A little word called, "Uh-uh."

681
00:47:16,733 --> 00:47:17,893
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, that's two words.

682
00:47:18,001 --> 00:47:21,869
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And here's a few more. Negative. No way. Nothing doing.

683
00:47:21,971 --> 00:47:24,872
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I ain't breaking my back to try and save "some pig,"

684
00:47:24,974 --> 00:47:28,239
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}no matter how "terrific" you think the little lunch meat is.

685
00:47:34,917 --> 00:47:36,782
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You'll sing a different tune when he's gone

686
00:47:36,886 --> 00:47:40,117
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and nobody brings around those scrumptious buckets of slop.

687
00:47:41,057 --> 00:47:43,457
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And three, two...

688
00:47:43,559 --> 00:47:45,186
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Cue the rat!

689
00:47:45,295 --> 00:47:47,160
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let's get one thing straight.

690
00:47:49,299 --> 00:47:51,096
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't care about the pig.

691
00:47:51,601 --> 00:47:54,092
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- What l care about is the slop. - Of course.

692
00:47:54,203 --> 00:47:58,196
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And since l'll be at the dump anyway, and it won't take any extra effort,

693
00:47:58,875 --> 00:48:02,504
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}maybe, maybe l'll pick something up.

694
00:48:03,479 --> 00:48:04,810
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're very kind.

695
00:48:05,615 --> 00:48:07,480
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't go spreading it around.

696
00:48:09,018 --> 00:48:11,486
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What? What do you want?

697
00:48:18,528 --> 00:48:20,223
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You'll need your strength.

698
00:48:25,268 --> 00:48:26,394
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thanks.

699
00:48:29,839 --> 00:48:31,602
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But, Dad, l heard them.

700
00:48:31,708 --> 00:48:33,403
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I heard them talking about the smokehouse!

701
00:48:33,509 --> 00:48:35,067
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's not your pig anymore.

702
00:48:35,178 --> 00:48:36,975
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, l wouldn't have sold him in the first place

703
00:48:37,080 --> 00:48:38,411
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}if l knew this is what they were gonna do to him.

704
00:48:38,514 --> 00:48:41,039
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's what happens to a pig on a farm, Fern.

705
00:48:42,585 --> 00:48:43,916
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You know that.

706
00:48:46,222 --> 00:48:47,689
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll see about that.

707
00:48:51,194 --> 00:48:54,891
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've got maybe two, three years before she can out-argue me.

708
00:48:55,331 --> 00:48:56,662
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Then l'm doomed.

709
00:48:57,100 --> 00:48:58,931
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And members of our own 4-H Club

710
00:48:59,035 --> 00:49:03,199
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}will have the opportunity to enter livestock and poultry in the competition.

711
00:49:03,306 --> 00:49:05,968
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So, in addition to the rides and games,

712
00:49:06,075 --> 00:49:08,600
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}make sure you show them your support, as well.

713
00:49:08,711 --> 00:49:10,770
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Any questions? Rita.

714
00:49:10,880 --> 00:49:12,541
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Miss Lewis, can l bring my chickens?

715
00:49:12,648 --> 00:49:16,049
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your chickens, l'm sure. Pigs, chickens, horses and cows.

716
00:49:16,152 --> 00:49:19,586
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You certainly can, and l hope you win first prize.

717
00:49:31,834 --> 00:49:35,065
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How can he be in every cornfield?

718
00:49:35,238 --> 00:49:37,502
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It can't be the same guy. It can't be!

719
00:49:37,673 --> 00:49:39,573
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's wearing the same hat.

720
00:49:39,675 --> 00:49:42,166
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm telling you, he is following us!

721
00:49:42,278 --> 00:49:44,041
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I hate that guy.

722
00:49:44,514 --> 00:49:47,506
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I have got to get some corn, Elwyn!

723
00:49:47,617 --> 00:49:49,414
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right! All right! All right! This is crazy.

724
00:49:49,519 --> 00:49:51,510
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- There's two of us, right? - Yeah.

725
00:49:51,687 --> 00:49:54,247
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Trust me, there's two of us, and there's only one of him.

726
00:49:54,357 --> 00:49:57,053
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't know, man. He scares me. He really does.

727
00:49:57,160 --> 00:49:59,720
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Just think about that corn. Corn. - Yeah.

728
00:49:59,829 --> 00:50:00,818
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- The corn. - Corn.

729
00:50:00,930 --> 00:50:04,331
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- All right, let's do it! - Let's do it! Let's do it!

730
00:50:08,438 --> 00:50:11,771
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Abort! Abort! Abort! - Abort! Abort! Abort!

731
00:50:14,444 --> 00:50:17,936
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Man, he is good! I bet he's laughing at us.

732
00:50:18,047 --> 00:50:20,777
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't look at him! Don't even give him the satisfaction.

733
00:50:20,883 --> 00:50:22,350
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just think about something else.

734
00:50:22,452 --> 00:50:24,249
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Think about something else. - Anything.

735
00:50:24,353 --> 00:50:26,844
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I think l see a rat.

736
00:50:26,956 --> 00:50:29,618
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- That's good. - No, really, l see a rat.

737
00:50:29,725 --> 00:50:34,424
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The rat is stealthy. The rat is nimble. The rat is on the... whoa!

738
00:50:41,504 --> 00:50:43,472
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The rat is losing his touch.

739
00:50:44,207 --> 00:50:47,904
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You want to go mess with him? - Oh, yeah! I've got to peck something.

740
00:50:48,010 --> 00:50:49,671
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Rat on three.

741
00:50:49,779 --> 00:50:51,940
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}One, two, three!

742
00:50:56,252 --> 00:50:57,947
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The rat has been spotted!

743
00:51:03,693 --> 00:51:05,217
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The rat is not

744
00:51:05,695 --> 00:51:07,253
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}enjoying this!

745
00:51:13,970 --> 00:51:15,494
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All this for slop?

746
00:51:15,605 --> 00:51:18,472
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The rat is desperate. The rat is trapped.

747
00:51:18,774 --> 00:51:21,436
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The rat needs to stop calling himself "the rat."

748
00:51:21,544 --> 00:51:25,275
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Find some words." Yeah, right, the rat will never find words!

749
00:51:25,681 --> 00:51:27,478
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey, look. Words.

750
00:51:30,353 --> 00:51:32,844
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Hey, is he still in the can? - He's in the can?

751
00:51:32,955 --> 00:51:35,753
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Maybe we should give him some privacy. Always helps me out.

752
00:51:35,858 --> 00:51:37,883
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, no, genius, not that can.

753
00:51:37,994 --> 00:51:40,053
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where did he go? I can't see him.

754
00:51:40,396 --> 00:51:42,330
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All l see is that fruit moving.

755
00:51:42,431 --> 00:51:44,956
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- What fruit? - The fruit with the tail!

756
00:51:45,334 --> 00:51:47,029
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They'll never get me now.

757
00:51:47,336 --> 00:51:51,033
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Let's go get him! - Go get him!

758
00:52:07,490 --> 00:52:09,287
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The rat rules!

759
00:52:11,327 --> 00:52:14,125
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- We're pink! - Hey, what the... Pink?

760
00:52:14,263 --> 00:52:18,393
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But that's all right, isn't it? I mean, black pretty much goes with everything.

761
00:52:18,501 --> 00:52:22,017
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, it's not all right. That rat is going to pay!

762
00:52:26,208 --> 00:52:27,402
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Radiant."

763
00:52:27,510 --> 00:52:29,375
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- This might just work. - Might?

764
00:52:29,478 --> 00:52:31,946
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, for the love of Lucy!

765
00:52:33,916 --> 00:52:36,544
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Here it comes. It did this yesterday.

766
00:52:36,819 --> 00:52:39,811
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look that way, everyone! Right towards that cloud!

767
00:52:39,922 --> 00:52:42,322
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Good gracious. Has it always done that?

768
00:52:42,425 --> 00:52:43,915
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, it can't have.

769
00:52:44,026 --> 00:52:47,484
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Brilliant! Absolutely brilliant! - Wow!

770
00:52:48,230 --> 00:52:49,390
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, yes.

771
00:52:49,498 --> 00:52:51,693
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This word will work quite nicely.

772
00:52:51,801 --> 00:52:54,031
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Then my work is done.

773
00:52:54,837 --> 00:52:56,862
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And now for the fruits of my labor.

774
00:52:56,973 --> 00:52:59,703
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And the vegetables! And the gravy!

775
00:53:25,101 --> 00:53:26,568
