{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Uncle.

904
01:01:28,817 --> 01:01:31,615
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Tell me, Uncle, what is the date of your birth?

905
01:01:33,956 --> 01:01:36,186
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your birthday?

906
01:01:39,461 --> 01:01:43,124
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}For heaven's sake, all l want to know is if you're a spring pig.

907
01:01:42,995 --> 01:01:48,000
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Of course. What did you think l was? A spring chicken?

908
01:01:49,938 --> 01:01:53,032
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Huge and humorous. Aren't we talented!

909
01:01:53,809 --> 01:01:55,401
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Spring chicken.

910
01:02:02,551 --> 01:02:05,042
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Charlotte, who are you talking to?

911
01:02:05,154 --> 01:02:08,453
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- The pig next door. - Should l be worried?

912
01:02:08,991 --> 01:02:11,289
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Of course not. What good would that do?

913
01:02:11,660 --> 01:02:14,823
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Whoa! Have you seen the beast next door?

914
01:02:14,930 --> 01:02:17,398
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I think his mama was part hippo.

915
01:02:16,987 --> 01:02:19,990
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If l had to name five of the fattest pigs l've ever seen,

916
01:02:19,902 --> 01:02:22,462
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}he'd be three of them. He's a shoo-in.

917
01:02:22,571 --> 01:02:25,734
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Please. That pig is not nearly as handsome as Wilbur,

918
01:02:26,041 --> 01:02:28,509
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}or as harmoniously proportioned,

919
01:02:28,610 --> 01:02:31,238
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- and not nearly as clean. - There's a real tiebreaker.

920
01:02:31,346 --> 01:02:35,373
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We just have to prove that the finest pig is not necessarily the fattest.

921
01:02:35,684 --> 01:02:38,380
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And you can do your part, Wilbur, by getting some rest.

922
01:02:38,487 --> 01:02:40,978
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I'm not tired, Charlotte. - Okay.

923
01:02:41,590 --> 01:02:44,457
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, could you excuse me for just a minute, please?

924
01:02:46,395 --> 01:02:50,092
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right, Templeton, you're right. That pig over there is a shoo-in.

925
01:02:50,199 --> 01:02:53,293
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So, l need words that are even better than that pig is fat.

926
01:02:53,402 --> 01:02:55,495
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Special words, and lots of them.

927
01:02:55,604 --> 01:02:57,799
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How about "pushy" and "demanding"?

928
01:02:57,906 --> 01:02:59,396
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Templeton, please!

929
01:02:59,508 --> 01:03:01,999
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This is our last chance to save Wilbur's life.

930
01:03:02,110 --> 01:03:04,670
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You do realize l'm just here for the food, right?

931
01:03:04,780 --> 01:03:06,077
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Of course.

932
01:03:22,097 --> 01:03:23,530
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Enjoy the ride.

933
01:03:24,566 --> 01:03:25,760
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}One, please.

934
01:03:26,034 --> 01:03:27,831
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Must be in the other pocket. Sorry.

935
01:03:27,936 --> 01:03:29,528
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- One second. - All right.

936
01:03:33,976 --> 01:03:35,273
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Two, please.

937
01:03:58,967 --> 01:04:00,525
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Is that Fern up there?

938
01:04:02,838 --> 01:04:04,237
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, l'll be.

939
01:04:04,339 --> 01:04:07,172
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- She's with a boy. - She is! She's with a boy!

940
01:04:10,312 --> 01:04:11,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, no.

941
01:04:13,048 --> 01:04:14,481
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She's with a boy.

942
01:04:16,218 --> 01:04:17,879
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Manna from heaven!

943
01:04:24,593 --> 01:04:27,221
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't know what this is, but l love it!

944
01:04:42,811 --> 01:04:44,403
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}One-stop slopping.

945
01:04:47,582 --> 01:04:51,712
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right. Let's go get the spider off my back.

946
01:04:52,854 --> 01:04:54,845
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}How come l'm not in a cornfield, Elwyn? How come?

947
01:04:54,956 --> 01:04:58,357
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey, hey. They got all kinds of corn right here.

948
01:04:58,460 --> 01:05:02,157
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You got your popcorn, caramel corn, candy corn.

949
01:05:02,264 --> 01:05:03,595
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Stop torturing me!

950
01:05:03,699 --> 01:05:07,328
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm starving here, and now l'm cross-eyed because of this pink stuff.

951
01:05:07,436 --> 01:05:09,404
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If l ever see that rat again...

952
01:05:09,738 --> 01:05:12,366
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Words, words, words.

953
01:05:13,108 --> 01:05:14,871
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Pork rinds."

954
01:05:15,377 --> 01:05:16,867
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That'll draw a crowd.

955
01:05:20,082 --> 01:05:21,777
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This looks promising.

956
01:05:25,921 --> 01:05:28,048
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey! That rat!

957
01:05:28,223 --> 01:05:30,851
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm going to get me some rat!

958
01:05:31,226 --> 01:05:33,217
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, not these birdbrains.

959
01:05:33,328 --> 01:05:34,989
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let's get rid of them once and for all.

960
01:05:35,097 --> 01:05:38,294
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}...and everything. Rat on three! Three!

961
01:05:39,267 --> 01:05:41,735
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wait up, Brooksie! L'm coming with you!

962
01:05:46,041 --> 01:05:47,872
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Little flamingoes!

963
01:05:48,877 --> 01:05:50,742
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come and get me!

964
01:05:51,646 --> 01:05:55,514
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- It's scary guy! - Abort! Abort!

965
01:05:57,085 --> 01:05:58,712
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Peck him! Peck him, Elwyn!

966
01:06:00,622 --> 01:06:05,252
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wait a minute. His eyes are buttons, and his hair is straw.

967
01:06:05,360 --> 01:06:06,384
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This guy ain't real!

968
01:06:06,495 --> 01:06:07,689
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- He's not? - No!

969
01:06:07,796 --> 01:06:11,232
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, yeah! The rat rules! Take that!

970
01:06:11,333 --> 01:06:12,664
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do you know what this means?

971
01:06:12,768 --> 01:06:13,860
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Yeah. - What?

972
01:06:13,969 --> 01:06:16,096
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We could've had corn!

973
01:06:19,374 --> 01:06:21,274
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, Your Highness, you satisfied or what?

974
01:06:21,376 --> 01:06:23,708
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}'Cause l've got a spitty hunk of pineapple upside-down cake out there

975
01:06:23,812 --> 01:06:24,904
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}with my name on it.

976
01:06:25,013 --> 01:06:26,810
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes, very satisfied.

977
01:06:27,382 --> 01:06:31,148
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Be careful. If you keep this up, someone might think you care.

978
01:06:31,486 --> 01:06:33,215
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Gee, l'm all choked up.

979
01:06:35,190 --> 01:06:36,248
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Charlotte?

980
01:06:36,691 --> 01:06:39,990
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If l don't win the prize tomorrow, they're gonna send me to the smokehouse.

981
01:06:40,095 --> 01:06:41,722
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're going to win, Wilbur.

982
01:06:41,830 --> 01:06:44,060
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And you're going to see the snows of winter.

983
01:06:44,166 --> 01:06:46,862
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I told you, l never break a promise.

984
01:07:05,253 --> 01:07:06,584
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mom?

985
01:07:06,988 --> 01:07:08,853
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Will you put these in for me?

986
01:07:12,227 --> 01:07:14,024
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You look like a girl!

987
01:07:14,696 --> 01:07:16,391
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And l still hit like one.

988
01:07:22,070 --> 01:07:23,935
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, what do you think?

989
01:07:24,039 --> 01:07:26,098
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's a great word. It's just...

990
01:07:26,241 --> 01:07:27,367
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just what?

991
01:07:27,509 --> 01:07:30,307
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Ls it the right word? Ls it true?

992
01:07:30,779 --> 01:07:32,110
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Because l don't really feel like

993
01:07:32,214 --> 01:07:35,149
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}l deserve any of the things you've written about me.

994
01:07:37,285 --> 01:07:39,253
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Then it is the perfect word.

995
01:07:43,959 --> 01:07:45,290
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The web!

996
01:07:48,296 --> 01:07:49,763
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey, Wilbur!

997
01:07:55,570 --> 01:07:56,594
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}"Humble."

998
01:07:56,705 --> 01:07:58,138
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey, Wilbur.

999
01:07:58,240 --> 01:08:00,834
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If that's not a prize-winner, l don't know what is.

1000
01:08:00,942 --> 01:08:02,705
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's going to win this thing, isn't he?

1001
01:08:02,811 --> 01:08:05,837
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, Homer, l can't go up to that grandstand looking like this.

1002
01:08:14,789 --> 01:08:15,813
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Homer.

1003
01:08:24,499 --> 01:08:26,023
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's not fair.

1004
01:08:30,672 --> 01:08:33,664
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why didn't they tell us the judging was going to be so early?

1005
01:08:35,310 --> 01:08:36,777
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We did our best.

1006
01:08:40,982 --> 01:08:43,610
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll get the truck and take him home.

1007
01:08:44,252 --> 01:08:46,220
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I really thought we had a shot.

1008
01:08:52,827 --> 01:08:55,660
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's okay. It'll be okay.

1009
01:08:59,167 --> 01:09:01,761
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I told you. There it is! The web!

1010
01:09:03,004 --> 01:09:04,437
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mom...

1011
01:09:07,175 --> 01:09:08,506
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What's going on?

1012
01:09:17,652 --> 01:09:20,883
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It looks like it's "humble."

1013
01:09:32,834 --> 01:09:36,031
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Excuse me. Thank you. Coming through. Excuse me.

1014
01:09:36,871 --> 01:09:39,806
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Mr. Zuckerman! Could you come with me, please?

1015
01:09:40,442 --> 01:09:42,637
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, and bring the pig, too.

1016
01:09:44,613 --> 01:09:45,580
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Homer.

1017
01:10:15,410 --> 01:10:19,574
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Ladies and gentlemen, on behalf of the state of Maine,

1018
01:10:19,681 --> 01:10:22,548
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}it gives us great pleasure to present

1019
01:10:22,651 --> 01:10:25,484
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Zuckerman's famous pig!

1020
01:10:31,159 --> 01:10:32,854
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Folks! Folks!

1021
01:10:33,161 --> 01:10:36,062
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I think we all remember the start of summer,

1022
01:10:36,164 --> 01:10:40,464
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}when the writing appeared on the web in Mr. Zuckerman's barn.

1023
01:10:40,835 --> 01:10:43,861
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And now it has happened yet again!

1024
01:10:44,506 --> 01:10:47,134
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Which is why the governors of the fair

1025
01:10:47,242 --> 01:10:49,039
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}are honored to present

1026
01:10:50,345 --> 01:10:52,313
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}this handsome medal.

1027
01:10:52,414 --> 01:10:56,874
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A token of our amazement and our appreciation.

1028
01:11:05,627 --> 01:11:07,060
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I love you, Wilbur.

1029
01:11:12,300 --> 01:11:15,861
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, what can l say about this pig that hasn't already been said?

1030
01:11:17,405 --> 01:11:20,306
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I know a lot of you folks have come out to the farm,

1031
01:11:20,408 --> 01:11:22,273
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and you've seen the words.

1032
01:11:22,377 --> 01:11:26,074
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A lot of you have asked me, "How could this have happened?"

1033
01:11:27,182 --> 01:11:28,581
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't know.

1034
01:11:28,983 --> 01:11:30,382
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But it has happened

1035
01:11:31,753 --> 01:11:36,087
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}in a time when we really don't see many miraculous things.

1036
01:11:36,791 --> 01:11:38,588
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Or maybe we do.

1037
01:11:39,227 --> 01:11:42,856
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Maybe they're all right there around us, every day,

1038
01:11:43,598 --> 01:11:45,828
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and we just don't know where to look.

1039
01:11:48,103 --> 01:11:51,732
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's no denying that our own little Wilbur,

1040
01:11:52,507 --> 01:11:55,601
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}he's part of something that's bigger than all of us.

1041
01:11:59,714 --> 01:12:01,614
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And life on that farm

1042
01:12:02,650 --> 01:12:05,118
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}is just a whole lot better with him in it.

1043
01:12:06,254 --> 01:12:09,121
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He really is some pig.

1044
01:12:09,624 --> 01:12:11,216
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Way to go, Wilbur!

1045
01:12:29,310 --> 01:12:32,370
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Charlotte, look how happy she is!

1046
01:12:32,480 --> 01:12:34,243
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Isn't that great?

1047
01:12:34,349 --> 01:12:36,249
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes, it's wonderful.

1048
01:12:37,051 --> 01:12:38,518
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey, what's that?

1049
01:12:38,720 --> 01:12:42,019
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This is my magnum opus.

1050
01:12:41,987 --> 01:12:43,989
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What's a magnet opus?

1051
01:12:45,293 --> 01:12:47,352
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Magnum opus.

1052
01:12:47,862 --> 01:12:51,798
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It means "great work." It's a nutrient-filled, waterproof egg sac.

1053
01:12:52,300 --> 01:12:54,268
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Really? There's eggs in there?

1054
01:12:54,369 --> 01:12:57,736
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My babies, 514 of them.

1055
01:12:57,839 --> 01:13:01,935
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wow! With 514 baby spiders all over the place,

1056
01:13:02,043 --> 01:13:04,375
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}it's going to be really radiant in the barn!

1057
01:13:04,479 --> 01:13:08,813
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wilbur, l'm afraid they're not going to make it back to the barn.

1058
01:13:08,917 --> 01:13:09,884
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What?

1059
01:13:10,018 --> 01:13:11,542
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What are you talking about?

1060
01:13:11,653 --> 01:13:13,951
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're not going to leave them here alone, are you?

1061
01:13:14,055 --> 01:13:16,649
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I have no choice. L'm languishing.

1062
01:13:17,258 --> 01:13:18,725
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What does that mean?

1063
01:13:19,194 --> 01:13:20,627
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It means l'm dying.

1064
01:13:21,095 --> 01:13:22,255
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What?

1065
01:13:22,831 --> 01:13:24,298
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You can't die!

1066
01:13:24,465 --> 01:13:27,832
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wilbur, we're born, we live,

1067
01:13:27,936 --> 01:13:30,131
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and, when our time comes, we die.

1068
01:13:30,672 --> 01:13:32,902
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's just the natural cycle of life.

1069
01:13:33,208 --> 01:13:35,768
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No! No, just climb down.

1070
01:13:35,877 --> 01:13:38,107
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll carry you the rest of the way.

1071
01:13:38,546 --> 01:13:41,743
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We'll go back to the barn, and l'll take care of you.

1072
01:13:41,850 --> 01:13:43,249
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, Wilbur.

1073
01:13:43,351 --> 01:13:45,876
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't even have the strength to climb down.

1074
01:13:46,221 --> 01:13:47,415
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You have to.

1075
01:13:48,089 --> 01:13:49,852
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You've done so much for me!

1076
01:13:50,191 --> 01:13:52,421
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And it was my great pleasure.

1077
01:13:52,861 --> 01:13:54,920
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Please come down, Charlotte.

1078
01:13:55,029 --> 01:13:57,497
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Please. There must be something l can do.

1079
01:13:57,599 --> 01:13:58,725
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, Wilbur.

1080
01:13:58,833 --> 01:14:01,097
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't you know what you've already done?

1081
01:14:01,202 --> 01:14:02,863
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You made me your friend,

1082
01:14:03,071 --> 01:14:07,167
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and, in doing so, you made a spider beautiful to everyone in that barn.

1083
01:14:09,277 --> 01:14:12,474
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I didn't do anything, Charlotte. You did it all.

1084
01:14:12,947 --> 01:14:16,474
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No. My webs were no miracle, Wilbur.

1085
01:14:16,851 --> 01:14:19,217
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I was only describing what l saw.

1086
01:14:19,954 --> 01:14:22,650
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The miracle is you.

1087
01:14:42,043 --> 01:14:43,340
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Templeton!

1088
01:14:43,845 --> 01:14:45,472
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Charlotte is very sick.

1089
01:14:45,747 --> 01:14:47,544
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yeah, and twisted.

1090
01:14:48,082 --> 01:14:50,949
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She's dying! She can't go home with us.

1091
01:14:51,052 --> 01:14:53,384
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So, l need you to help me take her egg sac with us.

1092
01:14:53,488 --> 01:14:54,716
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Did you say eggs?

1093
01:14:54,822 --> 01:14:57,052
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's an egg sac. And it's right up there,

1094
01:14:57,158 --> 01:14:58,785
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and it has her children in it.

1095
01:14:58,893 --> 01:15:02,124
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And l can't just leave it here. What if something happened to them?

1096
01:15:02,230 --> 01:15:05,097
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now, l can't reach it, so l need you to get it for me.

1097
01:15:05,199 --> 01:15:06,928
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And l need you to do it now.

1098
01:15:07,035 --> 01:15:08,502
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't think l like your tone.

1099
01:15:08,603 --> 01:15:12,334
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Can't you just once in your life think of someone other than yourself?

1100
01:15:12,440 --> 01:15:14,931


1101
01:15:15,510 --> 01:15:17,017
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on.

1102
01:15:16,711 --> 01:15:18,008
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No, you come on!

1103
01:15:18,279 --> 01:15:21,339
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Who got his hindquarters pecked to make you "radiant," huh?

1104
01:15:21,449 --> 01:15:22,916
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Templeton, that's who.

1105
01:15:23,017 --> 01:15:26,851
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And who interrupted the gorging of a lifetime so you could be "humble"?

1106
01:15:26,955 --> 01:15:29,617
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why, l think it was Templeton!

1107
01:15:29,724 --> 01:15:33,216
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Templeton! Templeton! Templeton!

1108
01:15:33,328 --> 01:15:34,955
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And do l get thanked?

1109
01:15:36,664 --> 01:15:37,722
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No!

1110
01:15:37,832 --> 01:15:39,561
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, has it ever occurred to you

1111
01:15:39,801 --> 01:15:43,430
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}that even a rat might like a little appreciation?

1112
01:15:43,538 --> 01:15:46,564
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A little, dare l say, love?

1113
01:15:46,674 --> 01:15:49,404
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do it and you'll get dibs on my slop for the rest of my life.

1114
01:15:49,510 --> 01:15:50,568
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Done.

1115
01:15:50,712 --> 01:15:53,044
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hurry! Up in the corner on the ledge.

1116
01:16:06,661 --> 01:16:07,923
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Templeton!

1117
01:16:14,068 --> 01:16:15,194
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on!

1118
01:16:24,479 --> 01:16:25,969
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank you, Templeton,

1119
01:16:27,648 --> 01:16:29,275
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}for everything.

1120
01:16:39,460 --> 01:16:41,587
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's okay, just drop it. Hurry!

1121
01:16:45,933 --> 01:16:47,901
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Here you go. Here's your medal.

1122
01:16:48,102 --> 01:16:50,627
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- In you go. - Time to go home, Wilbur.

1123
01:16:50,938 --> 01:16:53,372
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right. Close her up, Lurvy.

1124
01:16:55,309 --> 01:16:56,936
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Okay, easy now.

1125
01:17:10,625 --> 01:17:11,922
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Goodbye,

1126
01:17:12,827 --> 01:17:14,852
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}my sweet, sweet Wilbur.

1127
01:17:18,299 --> 01:17:19,823
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Goodbye, Charlotte.

1128
01:17:20,535 --> 01:17:22,093
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I love you.

1129
01:18:08,883 --> 01:18:12,046
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Is that our lovely-ovely-ovely little Wilbur?

1130
01:18:12,153 --> 01:18:14,713
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- And he's got a medal! - Strong work, kid.

1131
01:18:14,822 --> 01:18:16,187
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He looks so grown up.

1132
01:18:16,290 --> 01:18:18,850
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I always knew he could do it. - Never had a doubt.

1133
01:18:18,960 --> 01:18:20,518
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Welcome home, Wilbur.

1134
01:18:23,097 --> 01:18:24,325
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wilbur?

1135
01:18:24,832 --> 01:18:26,197
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where's Charlotte?

1136
01:18:26,300 --> 01:18:27,995
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I got a bad feeling, Bits.

1137
01:18:28,469 --> 01:18:29,936
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Me, too.

1138
01:19:27,695 --> 01:19:30,823
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now, that isn't to say Charlotte was gone forever.

1139
01:19:31,632 --> 01:19:33,725
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She lived on in the hearts of those that knew her,

1140
01:19:33,834 --> 01:19:36,200
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and even those that didn't.

1141
01:19:37,038 --> 01:19:39,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Something had changed in Somerset County.

1142
01:19:40,775 --> 01:19:44,267
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It was as if people knew they lived in a special place now.

1143
01:19:45,279 --> 01:19:48,976
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And, in small ways, they started being special people,

1144
01:19:49,884 --> 01:19:51,351
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}a little bit kinder,

1145
01:19:52,053 --> 01:19:54,078
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}a bit more understanding.

1146
01:19:55,122 --> 01:19:57,488
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And the animals felt different, too.

1147
01:19:57,959 --> 01:19:59,153
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Closer.

1148
01:20:00,294 --> 01:20:04,253
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The warmth of their friendship carried them through the long, cold months.

1149
01:20:05,299 --> 01:20:07,893
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They showed it in little gestures of kindness,

1150
01:20:08,369 --> 01:20:09,700
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}unusual patience,

1151
01:20:10,705 --> 01:20:12,138
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and promises kept.

1152
01:20:14,775 --> 01:20:18,404
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Even the hardest of hearts found themselves rising to the occasion.

1153
01:20:26,787 --> 01:20:30,154
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And, finally, the greatest promise of all,

1154
01:20:31,025 --> 01:20:34,586
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}a spring pig saw his first snowfall.

1155
01:20:36,297 --> 01:20:39,789
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It was as though Charlotte herself had shaken it out of the sky.

1156
01:21:11,532 --> 01:21:15,798
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The stillness of winter continued to the first thaw, like it always does.

1157
01:21:17,538 --> 01:21:19,904
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And then, the first buds of spring.

1158
01:21:21,709 --> 01:21:26,146
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And, before you knew it, life had come full circle.

1159
01:21:41,595 --> 01:21:43,563
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They're here! They're here!

1160
01:21:43,664 --> 01:21:45,427
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They're here, everybody!

1161
01:21:45,800 --> 01:21:49,133
{\fncambria\fs22\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey, there. L'm Wilbur. L'm a friend of your mom's.

1162
01:21:49,503 --> 01:21:52,131
